headline: PACCAR Q4 Earnings Match Estimates, Revenues Decline Y/Y
summary: PCAR's Q4 EPS match expectations, but revenues slide year over year as truck sales fall despite higher parts and services results.

headline: PCAR Q4 Deep Dive: Tariff Clarity and Aftermarket Growth Offset Truck Demand Weakness
summary: Trucking company PACCAR (NASDAQ:PCAR) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 13.7% year on year to $6.82 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.06 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
